{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_76","type":"agent_message","text":"The first-round reflection and serialization misses are gone, but the next run exposed a different problem during image build itself: pulling Janino’s compiler-discovery resource from its signed JAR causes native-image analysis to trip over `sun.security.x509.X509CertInfo`. I’m checking the build info and repository patterns now to see the cleanest way to satisfy Janino discovery without dragging signed-jar certificate state into the image."}}
